OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1772791513
OL,3,CCoroner 'perplexed' as Foreign Office
OL,4,Cfails to go to hearing for Kent
OL,5,Cbackpacker
OL,7,FMr Naughton said: "In fairness to the
OL,8,FForeign Office representative, it may
OL,9,Fbe that there is nothing more she can
OL,10,Fdo and the inquest may be hamstrung as
OL,11,Fcriminal proceedings continue in Laos."
OL,13,FDetective Sergeant Peter Duke, for the
OL,14,FJoint International Crime Centre, said
OL,15,Fhe was aware Ms White's travel
OL,16,Fcompanions, including her best friend
OL,17,FBethany Clarke, had been interviewed.
OL,26,@oD@SOUsD@gO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
